  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Gombi PHC - Yola Diocese</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at providing a comprehensive set of Primary Health Care services to improve the health status of poor people living in rural communities of Gombi. 

Services at the existing PHC will be expanded to include integrated health care services to an estimated population of 6,240 clients and community-based health services to be provided by a network of Village Health Workers and Traditional Birth Attendants in 5 selected communities. 

The project will also carry out community mobilisation activities to raise awareness on HIV/AIDS, primary health care, hygiene and water issues.

Technical competence of health staff will be enhanced through capacity building in such areas as health and management issues and counselling. The organization of community-based health care services will be strengthened through training and the provision of technical assistance for effective implementation of the project.

Towards the sustainability of the project, an annual 20% reduction in grant and development of sustainability strategy is incorporated in the project.</narrative>
  </description>
